{"source_key":"sha256-77a8d0a023ee41ad7912180250238aff","record_index":1972,"record_hash":"sha256:29d7afd64128a71a62eada138967d92cf4a893561f04b34f2dfa2ee9e8a007b7","timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.103Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"No edits made.\\n\\n**Findings**\\n\\nFix now: [crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12) re-exports the whole session-query API, but nothing outside `but-agentlog` uses it. That violates the playbook’s “public surface only what `but` needs.” Keep `Agent`, `Command`, `run_from_dir`; make `list_sessions`, `get_session_timeline`, related-session types/functions `pub(crate)` until there is a real caller.\\n\\nFix now: [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:121) uses overly generic public names: `TimelineTurn`, `RelatedTarget`, `Confidence`, `RelatedSession`. If these stay public, rename to concrete agentlog/session names, e.g. `AgentSessionTimelineTurn`, `AgentSessionRelatedTarget`, `AgentSessionMatchConfidence`.\\n\\nFix now: [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:235) clones every parsed record hash during duplicate filtering, including already-seen hashes on repeated captures. For growing JSONL logs this is the hot path. Use `contains` first, then clone only when inserting accepted records.\\n\\nFix now: [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:794) clones full `serde_json::Value` records out of the transcript map. These can include source records/tool payloads. Since timeline hydration returns owned values, prefer removing/moving from the map in record order.\\n\\nDocument/ignore for now: [crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:35) holds the capture lock through `capture_environment`, which can scan worktree state and up to 100 commits per branch at [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:299). That’s a concurrency/perf footgun for hook storms, but narrowing the lock safely needs a deliberate read/write race design, not a casual cleanup.\\n\\nLooks fine: `anyhow` is appropriate for this CLI-owned crate, error contexts are mostly good, and the internal environment/transcript types are sensibly `pub(crate)`/private.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.103Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}